<author><name><![CDATA[blargg]]></name></author>
<updated>2010-10-26T02:52:04-07:00</updated>
<published>2010-10-26T02:52:04-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6132&amp;p=69125#p69125</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6132&amp;p=69125#p69125"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Looking for PAL display that displays ALL pixels]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6132&amp;p=69125#p69125"><![CDATA[
When I was doing some PAL tests, I noticed that PAL forces black borders on the left and right; I don't think you can get anything but black. On NTSC, you can put anything there, including colored patterns if you move the PPU address around the $3Fxx region during that time. So a PAL emulator that shows anything but black is probably broken. I think PAL might even clip the left <em>active</em> column, though I didn't check that specifically.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Oct 26, 2010 2:52 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
